3 (6) (a) The Kentucky Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall post on its web
4 page evidence-based suicide prevention awareness information, to include
5 recognizing the warning signs of a suicide crisis. The web page shall include
6 information related to suicide prevention training opportunities offered by the
7 cabinet or an agency recognized by the cabinet as a training provider.
8 (b) Every public school and public charter school shall provide two (2) evidence-
9 based suicide prevention awareness lessons each school year, the first by
10 September 15 and the second by January 15, either in person, by live
11 streaming, or via a video recording to all students in grades six (6) through
12 twelve (12 ). Every public school shall provide an opportunity for any student
13 absent on the day the evidence-based suicide prevention awareness lesson was
14 initially presented to receive the lesson at a later time. The information may
15 be obtained from the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or from a
16 commercially developed suicide prevention training program.
17 (c) 1. Each school year, a minimum of one (1) hour of high-quality evidence-
18 based suicide prevention training, including risk factors, warning signs,
19 protective factors, response procedures, referral, postvention, and the
20 recognition of signs and symptoms of possible mental illness, shall be
21 required for all school district employees with job duties requiring direct
22 contact with students in grades four (4) through twelve (12). The
23 training shall be provided either in person, by live streaming, or via a
24 video recording and may be included in the four (4) days of professional
25 development under KRS 158.070. As used in this subparagraph,
26 "postvention" means a series of planned supports and interventions with
27 persons affected by a suicide for the purpose of facilitating the grieving
